import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    yearly_population = data.groupby('year')['people'].sum().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(yearly_population['year'], yearly_population['people'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the trend of population growth over the years?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    age_groups = data.groupby('age')['people'].sum()
    age_groups.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('People')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different age groups?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    male_data = data[data['sex'] == 1].groupby('age')['people'].sum()
    female_data = data[data['sex'] == 2].groupby('age')['people'].sum()
    
    plt.bar(male_data.index, male_data.values, label='Male')
    plt.bar(female_data.index, female_data.values, bottom=male_data.values, label='Female')
    
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('People')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of male and female population across different age groups?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data_pivot = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='age', values='people', aggfunc='sum')
    percentage_change = data_pivot.pct_change().fillna(0) * 100
    
    for age in percentage_change.columns:
        plt.plot(percentage_change.index, percentage_change[age], label=f'Age {age}')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage Change in Population')
    plt.title('What is the percentage change in population for each age group over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='best', title='Age Groups')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns=['sex', 'age'], values='people')
    data_pct_change = data.pct_change().fillna(0) * 100
    
    for sex in [1, 2]:
        for age in data_pct_change.columns.levels[1]:
            plt.plot(data_pct_change.index, data_pct_change[(sex, age)], label=f'Sex {sex}, Age {age}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage Change in Population')
    plt.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1), title='Sex, Age')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the percentage change in male and female population for each age group over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
